<title type="html"><![CDATA[Any programmer Interested?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6914&amp;p=66976#p66976"><![CDATA[
With Flash memory it's also possible to modify data without having to erase the Flash each time. This is achieved by representing the data in a way that changes only involve clearing bits. A simple approach is to store the byte or word value at the beginning of a 256-byte page. If it needs to be changed, store a zero over it and put the new value just after it. This assumes the value 0 can be used as a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sentinel_value" class="postlink">sentinel value</a>.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Mon Aug 30, 2010 7:40 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
