<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6914&amp;p=66966#p66966"><![CDATA[
The correct answer moves the player ahead in the chain. The correct answer won't be displayed upon the giving of a wrong answer, so the player can keep guessing. The player gets 3 tries in each chain. If all 3 tries are used up, the player cannot go further with the chain &amp; the results are put in the player's career stats.<br /><br />If you all have any further suggestions, let me know. You all sound very tech-savvy. &amp; tepples, I don't have any knowledge of programming, so you can let me know what the NES is capable of when it comes how many questions, answers, &amp; overall information it can handle. Whatever it takes to get on a cartridge and still look presentable, I could easily whittle down the # of questions I make for the game.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4551">Timmy112384</a> — Mon Aug 30, 2010 4:49 pm</p><hr />
